        JMJ / MMM     27 July 2010<br>Hello Brandon --<br>It has been my belief that in the final conclusion of Creation both all human beings and all angels will be saved, will attain to Heaven.<br><br>I believe that any words of Jesus we have will not militate against that belief.<br><br>As Catholics we are obliged to believe in the existence of hell. I believe there are some human beings in hell at this time .. And that there are fallen angels who are in hell at this time.<br><br>Let's consider Satan (Lucifer) as our extreme example. I ask myself whether or not God has graces not yet given to Satan that are far more powerful than any ever previously given to "the evil one." Shall we say no? Of course not.<br><br>And more than this. There is a kind of grace (I don't want to tangle about the name we will give it -- although I call it "infallibly efficacious grace") that causes a free will, freely, and infallibly, to do the good God wants. I believe this kind of grace was given to Mary at the Incarnation. That it was, now and then, given to Moses .. and that it was, now and then, given to St Paul .. and to others known to God.<br><br>Should God choose He could cause true repentance in Satan. It is my believe that God will do that. And if, in this extreme instance of one who damned him/her self, then with others possessed of less evil.<br><br>I will share with you a prayer I have been offering to God every morning for many years. "[COLOR="Blue"]Father, we beg You in the Name of Your Son Jesus Christ .. for the Eternal Salvation of all self-damned human beings ever to exist in all Your creation .. absolutely all, no exceptions.[/COLOR] AND [COLOR="blue"]Father, we beg You in the Name of Your Son Jesus Christ .. for the Eternal Salvation of all self-damned angels ever to exist in all Your creation .. absolutely all, no exceptions.[/COLOR]"<br><br>I may be mistaken in my belief. But I know God Loves all His creation .. and I hope very, very much that I am right.        John (JohnJFarren)</span>
